content: Doesn't work and my refund not provided. Waste of money
I've revised my review because I've found that suspending the mouse a few mm above the phone's screen makes it work (Microsoft wired red LED mouse).
It's not working for me and they aren't even refunding my amount...
This app does not work, should have listened to the reviews. Not everyone hords old computer junk.
replyContent: Please try an older wired mouse with a Red LED - most have one in a drawer or basement from old machine. A PC can have two mice. Try different angles for the mouse on the screen-my MS mouse only responds perpendicular to the screen. I have found mice with the Red led's work best. Some Blue LED work, but not many. Wireless mice usually don't work.
Thank you very much for your 5-star review!!! Please spread the word.

I have used a Dell and Microsoft mouse with this app with an old Motorola phone. Both work great. I really like that you can tune the Android display to minimize the mouse movement -- just enough to keep the screen saver happy, while moving the pointer just a few millimeters. I use two mice -- one that is always on top of the phone, and the other for regular use.
